  • Constructor Details

    • StringMutationComparator

      public StringMutationComparator​(boolean strictComparision)
      Create a StringMutationComparator. If strictComparison is set to TRUE, then only exact amino acid set matches will be considered equal. If set to FALSE, then if just one amino acid overlaps the two mutations will be considered equal. e.g. 46R will never equal 46T 46RS equals 46ST if strictComparison is set to FALSE, however they are not equal if it is set to TRUE 46RS equals 46RST regardless, because the smaller amino acid set of the two, is a subset of the larger
      Parameters:
      strictComparision -
